  "original_title": "\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0db4\u0dd9\u0da7\u0dca\u0d9a\u0ddd \u0dc4\u0dbb\u0dc4\u0dcf \u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0db6\u0dd9\u0daf\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dda \u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dc4\u0db1 \u0d89\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dbb\u0dd3\u0db8\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0db4\u0dc3\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Fuel is distributed through Cipetco only after the vehicles are removed",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to Mr. Kanchana Wijesekera, the Minister of Electricity and Energy, Sipetco will release fuel to consumers through fuel stations after removing the vehicles that are currently waiting in queues near the fuel stations.",
        "He also said that they have requested not to wait in queues near Sipetco fuel stations until the fuel is released.",
        "He also said that the distribution of fuel will start according to the vehicle number and after issuing the national fuel license. He said that the same procedure will be used to obtain fuel.",
        "\"The date of its implementation will be announced. It is not an easy task to set up the system and make it work. But in the next few months it should be implemented to ensure a weekly quota for everyone. Public support is needed to make this work smoothly and it will be improved as needed. have.\" He says on his Twitter account."
      ],
